# React Portals Conventions

## API base URL

- Every portal's axios client resolves baseURL as:
  `process.env.REACT_APP_API_URL || (dev ? 'http://127.0.0.1:8000' : window.location.origin)`.
- NEVER hard-code production API hosts or ports in portal code. Production serves
  API on the same origin via nginx `/api/` proxy — same-origin avoids the
  self-signed-cert and CORS failures we hit before.

## Build system

- All portals use Yarn 4 via corepack EXCEPT `admin-portal` (Yarn 1.22 classic,
  see its `packageManager` field). Run `corepack enable` before building.
- Build all portals with `./scripts/build-portals.sh` (sequential, one at a time,
  outputs to `deploy/dist/{customer,admin,agents,referrals}`).
- Builds must run with `CI=false` and `DISABLE_ESLINT_PLUGIN=true` — the codebase
  has ESLint warnings that CRA treats as errors when CI=true.
- NEVER build React portals on the production VPS (2GB RAM — it hangs for 30+ min).
  Build locally on the Mac, then deploy the compiled `deploy/dist/`.

## Error notifications

- Use `notifyHttpError(title, errorObj)` from the portal's notification service
  for API errors — don't roll custom alert handling.
